msgid "Updated at 2023-05-30"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:12
msgid ""
"\n"
"            Yatuk (“we,” “our,” or “us”) is committed to protecting your "
"privacy.\n"
"            This Privacy Policy explains how your personal information is "
"collected, used, and disclosed by Yatuk.\n"
"            This Privacy Policy applies to our website, and its associated "
"subdomains (collectively, our “Service”) alongside our \n"
"            application, Yatuk. By accessing or using our Service, you "
"signify that you have read, understood,\n"
"            and agree to our collection, storage, use, and disclosure of "
"your personal information as described\n"
"             in this Privacy Policy and our Terms of Service. This Privacy "
"Policy was created with Termify.\n"
"            "
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:22
#: .\core\templates\core\terms-and-conditions.html:33
msgid "Definitions and key terms"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:26
msgid ""
"Cookie:&nbsp;small amount of data generated by a website and saved by your "
"web browser. It is used to identify your browser, provide analytics, "
"remember information about you such as your language preference or login "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:27
msgid ""
"Company: when this policy mentions “Company,” “we,” “us,” or “our,” it "
"refers to Yatuk, Armenia, Shirak, Akhuryan, Petros Mkhoyan 1 line 7 building "
"that is responsible for your information under this Privacy Policy."
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:28
msgid ""
"Country: where Yatuk or the owners/founders of Yatuk are based, in this case "
"is Armenia"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:29
msgid ""
"Customer:&nbsp;refers to the company, organization or person that signs up "
"to use the Yatuk Service to manage the relationships with your consumers or "
"service users."
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:30
msgid ""
"Device:&nbsp;any internet connected device such as a phone, tablet, computer "
"or any other device that can be used to visit Yatuk and use the services."
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:31
msgid ""
"IP address: Every device connected to the Internet is assigned a number "
"known as an Internet protocol (IP) address. These numbers are usually "
"assigned in geographic blocks. An IP address can often be used to identify "
"the location from which a device is connecting to the Internet."
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:32
msgid ""
"Personnel:&nbsp;refers to those individuals who are employed by Yatuk or are "
"under contract to perform a service on behalf of one of the parties."
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:33
msgid ""
"Personal Data: any information that directly, indirectly, or in connection "
"with other information — including a personal identification number — allows "
"for the identification or identifiability of a natural person."
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:34
msgid ""
"Service: refers to the service provided by Yatuk as described in the "
"relative terms (if available) and on this platform."
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:35
msgid ""
"Third-party service:&nbsp;refers to advertisers, contest sponsors, "
"promotional and marketing partners, and others who provide our content or "
"whose products or services we think may interest you."
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:36
msgid ""
"Website: Yatuk’s site, which can be accessed via this URL: https://yatuk.am/"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:37
msgid ""
"You: a person or entity that is registered with Yatuk to use the Services."
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:42
msgid "What Information Do We Collect?"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:45
msgid ""
"\n"
"            We collect information from you when you visit our website, \n"
"            register on our site, place an order, subscribe to our \n"
"            newsletter, respond to a survey or fill out a form.\n"
"            <ul>\n"
"                <li>Name / Username</li>\n"
"                <li>Phone Numbers</li>\n"
"                <li>Email Addresses</li>\n"
"                <li>Password</li>\n"
"            </ul>\n"
"            "
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:58
msgid "How Do We Use The Information We Collect?"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:61
msgid ""
"\n"
"            <ul>\n"
"                <li>To personalize your experience (your information helps "
"us to better respond to your individual needs)</li>\n"
"                <li>To improve our website (we continually strive to improve "
"our website offerings based on the information and feedback we receive from "
"you)</li>\n"
"                <li>To improve customer service (your information helps us "
"to more effectively respond to your customer service requests and support "
"needs)</li>\n"
"                <li>To process transactions</li>\n"
"                <li>To administer a contest, promotion, survey or other site "
"feature</li>\n"
"                <li>To send periodic emails</li>\n"
"            </ul>\n"
"            "
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:73
msgid "When does Yatuk use end user information from third parties?"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:76
msgid ""
"\n"
"            Yatuk will collect End User Data necessary to provide the Yatuk "
"services to our customers.\n"
"            End users may voluntarily provide us with information they have "
"made available on social\n"
"             media websites. If you provide us with any such information, we "
"may collect publicly available \n"
"             information from the social media websites you have indicated. "
"You can control how much of your \n"
"             information social media websites make public by visiting these "
"websites and changing your privacy settings.\n"
"            "
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:85
msgid "When does Yatuk use customer information from third parties?"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:88
msgid ""
"\n"
"            We receive some information from the third parties when you "
"contact us. For example, when you \n"
"            submit your email address to us to show interest in becoming a "
"Yatuk customer, we receive \n"
"            information from a third party that provides automated fraud "
"detection services to Yatuk. \n"
"            We also occasionally collect information that is made publicly "
"available on social media \n"
"            websites. You can control how much of your information social "
"media websites make public \n"
"            by visiting these websites and changing your privacy settings.\n"
"            "
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:98
msgid "Do we share the information we collect with third parties?"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:101
msgid ""
"\n"
"            We may share the information that we collect, both personal and "
"non-personal, with third \n"
"            parties such as advertisers, contest sponsors, promotional and "
"marketing partners, \n"
"            and others who provide our content or whose products or services "
"we think may interest you. \n"
"            We may also share it with our current and future affiliated "
"companies and business partners, \n"
"            and if we are involved in a merger, asset sale or other business "
"reorganization, we may also \n"
"            share or transfer your personal and non-personal information to "
"our successors-in-interest.\n"
"\n"
"            We may engage trusted third party service providers to perform "
"functions and provide services \n"
"            to us, such as hosting and maintaining our servers and the "
"website, database storage and management, \n"
"            e-mail management, storage marketing, credit card processing, "
"customer service and fulfilling orders \n"
"            for products and services you may purchase through the website. "
"We will likely share your personal \n"
"            information, and possibly some non-personal information, with "
"these third parties to enable them to \n"
"            perform these services for us and for you.\n"
"            \n"
"            We may share portions of our log file data, including IP "
"addresses, for analytics purposes with \n"
"            third parties such as web analytics partners, application "
"developers, and ad networks. If your \n"
"            IP address is shared, it may be used to estimate general "
"location and other technographics such \n"
"            as connection speed, whether you have visited the website in a "
"shared location, and type of the \n"
"            device used to visit the website. They may aggregate information "
"about our advertising and what \n"
"            you see on the website and then provide auditing, research and "
"reporting for us and our advertisers. \n"
"            We may also disclose personal and non-personal information about "
"you to government or law enforcement \n"
"            officials or private parties as we, in our sole discretion, "
"believe necessary or appropriate in order \n"
"            to respond to claims, legal process (including subpoenas), to "
"protect our rights and interests or those \n"
"            of a third party, the safety of the public or any person, to "
"prevent or stop any illegal, unethical, or \n"
"            legally actionable activity, or to otherwise comply with "
"applicable court orders, laws, rules and regulations.\n"
"            "
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:130
msgid "Where and when is information collected from customers and end users?"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:133
msgid ""
"\n"
"            Yatuk will collect personal information that you submit to us. "
"We may also receive personal \n"
"            information about you from third parties as described above.\n"
"            "
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:139
msgid "How Do We Use Your Email Address?"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:142
msgid ""
"\n"
"            By submitting your email address on this website, you agree to "
"receive emails from us. \n"
"            You can cancel your participation in any of these email lists at "
"any time by clicking on the \n"
"            opt-out link or other unsubscribe option that is included in the "
"respective email. \n"
"            We only send emails to people who have authorized us to contact "
"them, either directly, \n"
"            or through a third party. We do not send unsolicited commercial "
"emails, because we hate \n"
"            spam as much as you do. By submitting your email address, you "
"also agree to allow us to \n"
"            use your email address for customer audience targeting on sites "
"like Facebook, where we \n"
"            display custom advertising to specific people who have opted-in "
"to receive communications \n"
"            from us. Email addresses submitted only through the order "
"processing page will be used for \n"
"            the sole purpose of sending you information and updates "
"pertaining to your order. If, however, \n"
"            you have provided the same email to us through another method, "
"we may use it for any of the purposes \n"
"            stated in this Policy. Note: If at any time you would like to "
"unsubscribe from receiving future emails, \n"
"            we include detailed unsubscribe instructions at the bottom of "
"each email.\n"
"            "
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:159
msgid "How Long Do We Keep Your Information?"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:162
msgid ""
"\n"
"            We keep your information only so long as we need it to provide "
"Yatuk to you and fulfill the purposes described in this policy. This is also "
"the case for anyone that we share your information with and who carries out "
"services on our behalf. When we no longer need to use your information and "
"there is no need for us to keep it to comply with our legal or regulatory "
"obligations, we’ll either remove it from our systems or depersonalize it so "
"that we can’t identify you.\n"
"            "
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:167
msgid "How Do We Protect Your Information?"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:170
msgid ""
"\n"
"            We implement a variety of security measures to maintain the "
"safety of your personal information when you place an order or enter, "
"submit, or access your personal information. We offer the use of a secure "
"server. All supplied sensitive/credit information is transmitted via Secure "
"Socket Layer (SSL) technology and then encrypted into our Payment gateway "
"providers database only to be accessible by those authorized with special "
"access rights to such systems, and are required to keep the information "
"confidential. After a transaction, your private information (credit cards, "
"social security numbers, financials, etc.) is never kept on file. We cannot, "
"however, ensure or warrant the absolute security of any information you "
"transmit to Yatuk or guarantee that your information on the Service may not "
"be accessed, disclosed, altered, or destroyed by a breach of any of our "
"physical, technical, or managerial safeguards.\n"
"            "
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:175
msgid "Could my information be transferred to other countries?"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:178
msgid ""
"\n"
"            Yatuk is incorporated in Armenia. Information collected via our "
"website, through direct interactions with you, or from use of our help "
"services may be transferred from time to time to our offices or personnel, "
"or to third parties, located throughout the world, and may be viewed and "
"hosted anywhere in the world, including countries that may not have laws of "
"general applicability regulating the use and transfer of such data. To the "
"fullest extent allowed by applicable law, by using any of the above, you "
"voluntarily consent to the trans-border transfer and hosting of such "
"information.\n"
"            "
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:183
msgid "Is the information collected through the Yatuk Service secure?"
msgstr ""

#: .\core\templates\core\privacy-policy.html:186
msgid ""
